(77,2025,24,324,'5','Physical Chem: Quantum Mechanics & Spect','Craig Teague',1,'CHE',NULL,'Physical Chemistry: Quantum Mechanics & SpectroscopyThermodynamics and descriptions of systems of equilibria from both classical and statistical perspectives, molecular and atomic spectroscopy, quantum mechanics, atomic structure, and theories of reaction rates. This course has both classroom and laboratory components. This course also satisfies a 300-level PHY major requirement.','MAT 121, CHE 122, CHE 161','Science'),
(78,2025,25,261,'6','Global Environmental Economics','James Goodenberger',1,'ECB',NULL,'Economic analysis of global environmental issues, with special emphasis on developing countries. Review of basic economic theory with respect to environmental issues. Policy analysis of sustainable development, population growth, deforestation, air and water pollution, ecotourism, international hazardous waste, biodiversity, and global warming.  Alternate years.','ECB 101, ECB 102','Social Science'),
