(82,2025,24,121,'5','Chemical Principles I','Catherine Volle, Harmeet Bhoday',1,'CHE',NULL,'Fundamental concepts of chemistry, mole concept, energy, theories of the atom and the chemical bond, and molecular geometry. This course is intended primarily for those considering a major in science. CHE 121 utilizes concepts from high school algebra I and II.','','Science, Quantitative Reasoning Encounter'),
(83,2025,15,222,'8','Digital Photography','Alex McKenzie',1,'ART',100,'This course explores the basic concepts of digital photography as a form of creative expression. Students will explore the composition of photographic images along with digital editing and manipulation processes. This course has an additional materials fee of approximately $100 per student. No alternative grade option.','ART 103, ART 104, ART 110, ART 115, ART 200','Fine Arts'),
(84,2025,20,487,'7','Senior Thesis','Chris Penn-Goetsch',1,'ART',NULL,'A substantial capstone project to be completed during the senior year. Studio majors conceive, create, and mount an exhibition of a new body of work. Art history majors research an art historical problem, write a research paper, prepare an abstract, and provide a public presentation of their work with the goal of creating an original contribution to the discipline. An oral defense is required for either major. No alternative grade option. The Studio Art section is pre-approved for transcript notation in the Ingenuity in Action category, Creative Expression. The Art History section is pre-approved for transcript notation in the Ingenuity in Action category, Research. To participate and earn notation of completion on your transcript, please complete the Ingenuity in Action application.','ART 483, ART 392','Ingenuity in Action, Creative Expression, Ingenuity in Action, Research'),
(85,2025,25,762,'Adjunct Fall','Piano','Jessica Monnier',0.5,'MUS',NULL,'No alternate grade option. Lesson Fees: Please note that students who are not music scholarship recipients ($3,000+) are responsible for paying a lesson fee. These fees are the same for lessons on secondary instruments.  Recipients of music scholarships will not be charged for lessons on their principal (scholarship audition) instrument.','','Fine Arts'),
(86,2025,25,347,'1','Mathematical Statistics I','Ann Cannon',1,'STA',NULL,'Typically the first term covers probability, random variables, sampling distributions and collecting data. The second term covers theory of estimation and hypothesis testing, linear and multiple regression, analysis of variance, and techniques for categorical data. Alternate years. ','MAT 122, MAT 221','Fine Arts, Writing Encounter, First-Year Seminar'),
(87,2025,18,155,'8','Contemporary Songwriting','Christopher Nakielski',1,'MUS',280,'This course is designated for aspiring singer/songwriters who have an interest in pop and commercial music, including rap. This class will focus on how to craft a successful pop contemporary song through targeted songwriting assignments, which includes heavy instruction on writing lyrics. This course will also put heavy emphasis on collaborations, along with daily professional and peer-to-peer critiques of each student\'s work in-progress. This class will conclude with a three day trip to downtown Chicago to record students\' tunes at a reputable Chicago recording studio. There are no official prerequisites but having some basic facility over your instrument (knowing a four-chord progression) or voice (singing in tune) is helpful. If you don\'t play an instrument and make music by your own means of electronic construction, this is acceptable. If you\'re solely a lyricist, this too is acceptable, and we will pair you up with a collaborator that plays an instrument. Please know that there are no texts required for purchase for this course, so please take that into consideration when justifying the additional fee per student, which covers hotel, professional studio musicians and engineers, and recording studio rental; ultimately, this is an incredible value.','','Fine Arts'),
(88,2025,25,142,'5','Foundations: Organismal Biology','Rebecca Richtsmeier-Ross, Isaac Winkler',1,'BIO',NULL,'The topics of genetics, evolution, speciation, classification, the diversity of life, ecology, biological communities, and animal behavior. This course is a prerequisite for all upper-level Biology courses.','','Science'),
(89,2025,25,153,'8','Origins of the American Nation','Phil Lucas',1,'HIS',NULL,'From colonial origins through Reconstruction, with emphasis on the formation of local, sectional, and national communities. No alternative grade option. Not open to seniors without permission of the instructor.','','Humanities, Intercultural Literacy Encounter'),
