(106,2025,25,357,'2','The Boom & Post Boom in Latin America','Michael Mosier',1,'SPA',NULL,'This class analyzes the explosive literary phenomenon of the 60s and 70s known as the “Boom.” Students will read a selection of works by authors such as Gabriel Garcia Marquez, Julio Cortázar, and Carlos Fuentes with an emphasis on magic realism. Furthermore, we will explore literary trends that follow the Boom generation.  Offered every third year. ','SPA 311','Humanities'),
(107,2025,99,702,'Adjunct Fall','Composition','Drew Bonner',0.5,'MUS',NULL,'Original composition for various media, beginning with smaller forms. May be repeated for credit. This course may be taken for 0.25, 0.5 or 1.0 credits.  No alternate grade option.','','Fine Arts'),
(108,2025,100,502,'Adjunct Fall','Academic Success','Cindy Turley',0.25,'INT',NULL,'Want to brush up or develop skills for your academic toolbox? Want to take an adjunct course for 1/4 credit? Join us as we share practical information to help you become more successful in the classroom. We will have various speakers share their knowledge on a toolbox topic including relevant information you can use in your current classes. Topics include time management, effective study methods, growth mindset, test taking strategies, and more! This class will work alongside your block courses throughout the semester. This course takes place on the first, second, and third Friday of each block of the first semester from 11:45-12:45 OR from 3:15-4:15. You choose the time that works with your schedule!','',''),
