(221,2025,25,487,'3','Senior Seminar','Erin Davis',1,'SOC',NULL,'The senior capstone course provides sociology majors an opportunity to reflect on their academic career as their attention turns toward their post-baccalaureate future.  It is designed to help students synthesize, integrate, and articulate their sociological insights and experiences. The course is organized around three major themes: (1) reflection and assessment of one’s academic career, (2) professional development; and (3) a cumulative capstone project.  Open only to Senior Sociology Majors. No alternate grade option.','Two 300 level courses in Sociology','Social Science'),
