(387,2025,25,515,'Adjunct Fall','Literary Citizenship','Rebecca Entel',0.25,'ENG',NULL,'Attendance at a minimum number of literary arts events each semester (determined by the faculty), participation in a writing group or relevant student organization, film screenings, book arts workshops, and the production of reflective and/or creative work in response to those events will be required for credit. Majors are required to register for two semesters of the adjunct course (.25 credit per semester); semesters need not be consecutive. Students will participate in a minimum of 12.5 contact hours including events, workshops, and other pertinent meetings, and undertake a total of 37.75 total hours of work. Course is assessed as credit/no credit.','',''),
