(613,2025,25,440,'4','Student Teaching IV','Elizabeth Globokar',1,'EDU',NULL,'A 14-week clinical teaching experience under the direction of Cornell faculty and certified K-12 school teachers in approved elementary or secondary schools, taken in conjunction with EDU 420 & EDU 430. Attendance at a bi-weekly evening seminar is required. These three courses (EDU410, 420, & 430) must be scheduled in consecutive terms during the senior year or during a fifth year. Required for a teaching certification recommendation in the State of Iowa. Students must provide their own transportation. EDU 440 may be required or taken as an option, specific student requests/requirements. All 200- and 300-level Education courses and approval of the Education Department.This course is pre-approved for transcript notation in Ingenuity in Action.  To participate and earn notation of completion on your transcript, please complete the Ingenuity in Action application.','EDU 430','CR, Teacher Preparation'),
(614,2025,25,362,'8','Statistical Learning','Tyler George',1,'STA',NULL,'This course will introduce students to relatively new and powerful statistical techniques used to analyze data. The course will begin with a review of linear regression and an introduction to computer-based variable and model selection methods. Other topics will include classification methods, resampling methods for model-building, non-linear models, and tree-based methods. The computer software program R will be used throughout.Alternate years.','STA 202, DSC 223, STA 223, CSC 223',NULL),
