(681,2025,18,215,'1','Introduction to Creative Writing','Scott Morris',1,'ENG',NULL,'Beginning course in creative writing and an introductory course to the English major. Students will explore a myriad of writing techniques and approaches to writing in a variety of genres. Students will write, share work, and offer critiques. The course also includes the study of published authors as models for student writing, as literary historical context for artistic creation, and for the study of creative theory. Students will learn to analyze texts from a writer’s perspective, which they will apply to their own writing and to the study of literature in the major.Required for English Major concentrators in Creative Writing.','','Fine Arts, Writing Encounter'),
(682,2025,20,102,'4','Beginning Spanish II','Alyssa Selmer',1,'SPA',NULL,'Essentials of grammar stressing skills in understanding, speaking, reading, and writing with classroom activities promoting conversational skills. Short readings for cultural awareness and vocabulary development.','SPA 101, SPA 101C','Language'),
(683,2025,18,304,'8','Secondary Foreign Language Methods','Jill Heinrich',1,'EDU',NULL,'This course explores the theory and practice of teaching and learning a foreign language in the secondary school setting.  Topics will include instructional strategies for teaching conversational skills and cultural appreciation in the target language, and learning theory as it relates to the study of foreign language. This course is conducted at the practicum site. Transportation to and from the practicum site is the responsibility of the student.Course is graded Credit/No Credit.','EDU 301, EDU 328','Credit/No Credit'),
(684,2025,25,353,'6','Business Analytics I','Santhi Hejeebu',1,'ECB',NULL,'This course introduces the data mining process used in industry as well as a variety of algorithms and statistical techniques used predict business outcomes. The course will cover the basics of the data mining process including data preprocessing, partitioning and model performance evaluation. The course also introduces several common methods used to predict numerical and categorical outcomes. Methods include regression techniques, k-Nearest Neighbor, Naïve Bayes and others.','STA 202, STA 348',NULL),
(685,2025,25,275,'7','General Physics II','Mazhar Iqbal',1,'PHY',NULL,'Continuation of PHY 225 and PHY 245. Topics include relativity and electricity and magnetism.','PHY 245','Science'),
(686,2025,25,323,'5','History of Western Music Romantic/20th C','James Martin',1,'MUS',NULL,'Chronological development of Western music from the Romantics to the present. Emphasis on historical, cultural, aesthetic, and structural examination of musical works; and the development of genres, forms and performance practices. No alternate grade option. Offered in alternate years. MUS 321, MUS 322, and MUS 323 may be taken in any order.','ENG 111, WREQ, WRT 016, WRT 100, MUS 310','Humanities, Writing Encounter'),
(687,2025,16,334,'3','Biochemistry','Diane Gingerich Feil, Collin O\'Leary',1,'CHE',NULL,'Cellular metabolism, with emphasis on energy extraction pathways and energy homeostasis. The approach is primarily mechanistic with a quantitative discussion of kinetics, free-energy changes, and the electrochemistry of electron transport chains. ','BIO 205, CHE 327','Science'),
(688,2025,25,774,'Adjunct Spring','Guitar','Tom Nothnagle',0.25,'MUS',NULL,'No alternate grade option. Lesson Fees: Please note that students who are not music scholarship recipients ($3,000+) are responsible for paying a lesson fee. These fees are the same for lessons on secondary instruments.  Recipients of music scholarships will not be charged for lessons on their principal (scholarship audition) instrument.','','Fine Arts'),
(689,2025,25,271,'4','Engineering Thermodynamics','Niloofar Kamran',1,'EGR',NULL,'Thermodynamics is the study of energy and its conversion to other forms, notably work and heat.  Topics include internal energy, enthalpy, entropy and temperature; the first and second laws of thermodynamics; combustion, cyclic processes, engines, efficiency and refrigeration; heat transfer. Practical applications of thermodynamics are also discussed, including power generation, pollution and waste control, materials science and chemical engineering.','PHY 225',''),
(690,2025,25,731,'Adjunct Spring','Trombone: Brass Instruments','Drew Bonner',0.25,'MUS',NULL,'No alternate grade option. Lesson Fees: Please note that students who are not music scholarship recipients ($3,000+) are responsible for paying a lesson fee. These fees are the same for lessons on secondary instruments.  Recipients of music scholarships will not be charged for lessons on their principal (scholarship audition) instrument.','','Fine Arts'),
